CLASS_SYMT licensing
====================

This repository contains two bodies of work.

1. CLASS (Cosmic Linear Anisotropy Solving System)
   Copyright (c) Julien Lesgourgues, Thomas Tram, Nils Schoeneberg,
   and contributors.

   The unmodified portions of this repository are the public CLASS code
   (https://github.com/lesgourg/class_public), distributed by its
   authors without a formal license under the following terms, which
   apply here unchanged: CLASS may be used freely, provided that
   publications using it cite at least "CLASS II: Approximation
   schemes", D. Blas, J. Lesgourgues, and T. Tram, JCAP 07 (2011) 034,
   arXiv:1104.2933. All rights in the original CLASS code remain with
   its authors.

2. CLASS_SYMT modifications (the afterglow memory species)
   Copyright (c) 2025-2026 Thomas Glenn Martin and In-Gyu Koh.

   The modifications comprise the afterglow background and perturbation
   modules, the associated input handling, the unit suite
   (test/test_afterglow_bg.py, test/test_afterglow_pt.py), and the
   accompanying documentation. These modifications are released under
   the MIT License:

